Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.22,0:00:05.50,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hi, everybody, my name is Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.60,0:00:10.58,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ah... otherwise known as Britjet on PSX forums.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.58,0:00:14.98,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm a retired BA(British Airways) 747 pilot and ...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.98,0:00:16.84,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,playing with PSX
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.84,0:00:20.56,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I am not sure that's the right word, because it's so realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.56,0:00:22.86,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,certainly got me hooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.86,0:00:26.49,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I thought I put together, some videos
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:28.77,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,showing some aspects of the operation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.77,0:00:31.25,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,the 747 which might not be immediately obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.25,0:00:34.20,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,in various manuals you can get you hands on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:35.37,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,Health warning:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.37,0:00:39.69,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,any pros watching this trying to glean some information\Nfor your next check
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:42.49,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,Please don't, just use your own SOPs and your knowledges
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.25,0:00:45.70,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's equally as good as mine if not much better
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:47.76,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is just for fun, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:51.78,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,This particular approach is, e...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.13,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,onto 27L Heathrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.13,0:00:55.86,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,all LOC on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.86,0:00:58.21,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,And ATCs are gonna tell us or ask us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.21,0:01:01.08,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,to go for 27R.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:03.54,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,There are also some bottom lines to this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.54,0:01:05.54,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't do it in bad weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.54,0:01:07.72,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,you couldn't be able to see the other runway
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:09.72,英文字幕,,0,0,0,,And don't trying do this below 2000ft
